reviews.subject: Mathematics
reviews.review: Dr. Johnson is amazing at explaining complex concepts. Her lectures are clear and engaging.

reviews.subject: Physics
reviews.review: Prof. Khan is very knowledgeable, though his lectures can sometimes be a bit fast-paced.

reviews.subject: Chemistry
reviews.review: Dr. Davis is good, but her grading is quite strict. You need to work hard to score well.

reviews.subject: Computer Science
reviews.review: Dr. Smith is the best professor I've had. His programming assignments are challenging but rewarding.

reviews.subject: History
reviews.review: Prof. Brown knows her subject well. Her classes are interesting, but there's a lot of reading.

reviews.subject: Economics
reviews.review: Dr. Thompson makes economics fun and relevant. His lectures are always insightful.

reviews.subject: Statistics
reviews.review: Prof. Raza's lectures are difficult to follow, and he doesn't provide much help outside of class.

reviews.subject: Philosophy
reviews.review: Dr. White is a great professor, but her classes require deep thinking and lots of participation.

reviews.subject: Biology
reviews.review: Prof. Lee is knowledgeable, but his exams are tough. Study hard and attend all lectures.

reviews.subject: Psychology
reviews.review: Dr. Garcia is fantastic! She connects theory with real-world examples, making the subject easy to understand.

reviews.subject: Sociology
reviews.review: Prof. Patel encourages discussions and debates, which makes the class engaging. However, the workload is heavy.

reviews.subject: Engineering
reviews.review: Dr. Miller's lectures are detailed, but sometimes hard to understand. His office hours are helpful though.

reviews.subject: Art History
reviews.review: Prof. Williams is passionate about art. His classes are interesting and visually stimulating.

reviews.subject: Environmental Science
reviews.review: Dr. Moore is very knowledgeable. Her classes are informative, but her exams are tricky.

reviews.subject: Business Management
reviews.review: Prof. Mehta is an excellent professor. He has real-world experience that he brings into his teaching.

reviews.subject: English Literature
reviews.review: Dr. Taylor has a deep understanding of literature. Her classes are insightful, but there's a lot of reading.

reviews.subject: Political Science
reviews.review: Prof. Wong's classes are content-heavy. You need to stay up-to-date with the readings to do well.

reviews.subject: Pharmacology
reviews.review: Dr. Clark is an excellent teacher. Her classes are challenging, but she explains the material very well.

reviews.subject: Astronomy
reviews.review: Prof. Taylor's lectures are fascinating. He has a way of making complex concepts easy to understand.

reviews.subject: Anthropology
reviews.review: Dr. Adams is knowledgeable, but her lectures can be a bit dry. Her exams are fair, though.

reviews.subject: Computer Science
reviews.review: Great teacher, great material

reviews.subject: Psychology
reviews.review: Had her for the first five-week summer session. One thing I liked about her for the summer class was that there weren't a lot of assignments since there were case studies, a TED talk video, 3 exams, and there was a research project that was due by the end of the term.

reviews.subject: History
reviews.review: Glad she is gone. What a waste of our dollars to not be taught how to write a paper.

reviews.subject: Secondary Education
reviews.review: Dr. Duckor is a gem of a professor, one of the best in the doctoral program at SJSU. He is deeply knowledgeable and yet approachable, kind, and funny. He sets you at ease even while he helps doctoral students wade through the finer points of assessing assessments. He is a master at his craft and I would happily take another course from him!!

reviews.subject: Psychology
reviews.review: Dr. CCF is an excellent teacher. Attendance isn't mandatory but necessary for success. She gives lots of resources like lecture outlines/slides and opportunities to use cheat sheets for tests/final. Many people mistake her teaching style as being difficult when it is actually super dense course content. Be prepared to study and do her extra credit!

reviews.subject: Accounting
reviews.review: He grades on 3 midterms and joining the IMA club. He used to be an executive for a utilities company in Maine. You gotta take him, he gives a real world, business perspective for the class. He's also extremely knowledgeable in life tips and making it to the top in the industry. If you want to learn more than just the textbook, take Carroll.

reviews.subject: Philosophy
reviews.review: RIP. Professor Sonnier passed away recently.

reviews.subject: Accounting
reviews.review: He's really Amazing! A must have course!!

reviews.subject: Computer Science
reviews.review: 1 of my most fav classes ever. For a dry subject, I ended up enjoying the topic and learned a lot. Very accessible & provides advice about the industry/jobs. He also includes diversity in his lectures, so you learn about more than just computability. Not a hard class when you attend the lectures - he explains things very well.

reviews.subject: History
reviews.review: He is totally approachable and understanding. He is super friendly and knowledgable about the information. He does a great job of staying focused on the material while relating it to present day and explaining how its playing a role. He really cares about his students and presents the content in a digestible way.
